The mother of baby Siwaphiwe Mbambo and two other people will appear in the Durban Magistrate s Court on Monday on charges of hijacking and kidnapping police said.Additional charges might be added against the three suspects they said. One-month-old Siwaphiwe was found in the early hours of Sunday after police intercepted a vehicle near Mariannhill Toll Plaza two days after she was snatched during a car hijacking at a Durban shopping centre.Her biological mother S bongile Mbambo was taken into custody on Saturday while the two occupants of the vehicle stopped by police on Sunday morning were also arrested.